702292f-b.title: Brooklyn: 3rd Avenue - 36th Street.
702292f-b.text:
3rd Avenue (left), north from 36th Street. The buildings
on the east side of the avenue were all torn down to make way
for the construction of Gowanus Parkway, Brooklyn's northerly
link in the Belt Parkway system of highways. On the west side
of the avenue are the Bush Terminal buildings.
View 2 is north from 34th Street and view 3 shows a close-
up of one of the Bush Terminel buildings.
October, 1940
Views 1,2,3
P. L. Sperr
